<br>
You see...<br>
<br>
My father is in the U.S. Navy, and has been for 25 years, and he sent me a letter stating :<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> <br>
<br>
I just thought I would write and let you know where I am and what I am doing.  Currently, I am aboard the USS McFaul, which is one of the new Aegis class Destroyers.  The McFaul has been commissioned for a little over 2 years, and is already on its second deployment overseas.  Right now, we are sitting right off the coast of Iraq and Iran, with a job of intercepting likely smugglers who would run with Iraqi oil and make extra money for Saddam Hussien.  All I can tell you is that there are plenty of them trying to run the blockade and we catch alot of them.  This week, two of them sank themselves or set fire to themselves to prevent us from boarding them and taking the ship to a port for disposition of the oil.  The sky is always hazy from the smoke of burning wells, and there are huge slicks of oil along the of the ocean from the ships that have sunk near our position.<br>
<br>
Speaking of boardings, most of these people are Arabs of one sort or another.  We had teams on board other ships when the events in the news occured.  It was very disturbing for our crew to see Arabs celebrating the death and destruction that was happening back home.  It really puts things into perspective that these people hate us more than we would ever imagine.  I have no doubt that Arab terrorists who wanted to strike a blow at the mighty oppressor, the USA, performed the acts.<br>
<br>
Maybe one day we will know who for sure it was, but I can assure you that they are international heroes over in the Middle East.  They resort to this terrorism as it is the poor man's weapon of choice, and they sure don't mind dying for their cause.  Someday down the road,there will be enough information to qualify someone for a large strike in retaliation.<br>
<br>
When that happens, we will be ready to deliver all we got to make our contribution to this end.  The most saddening thing is that no matter what we do, they have had their victory.  We cannot destroy very much because they have nothing that would even come close to what was once the twin towers.  They have nothing like the pentagon.  We will only spend more billions on missiles and bombs to counter the death and destruction they have caused with a handful of volunteers and a box of knives.  It's a world of evil we live in today.  We will have to learn a lot from these lessons.<br>
<br>
Defender of Freedom...<br>
(one of many)<br>
Tim Anderson<br>
<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
This scares me, not knowing if I'll see my dad again if anything goes down.  I'm 24 years old, and tears come to my eyes every time I think of that.<br>
<br>
All of us will have these images burned into our brains for the rest of our lives.  We will all know where we were and what happened on the morning of September 11th, 2001.  Maybe someday we will hear about a trial, or see some final result of what we can say for sure happened.  Some things we may never know.  Thousands of people disappeared off the face of the earth, we may never know how many.  This act was certainly part of a bigger plan, and I am sure there is more to follow.<br>
<br>
All I can say is, stand tall, work together to make this country get back on its feet again, and be proud to be an American.  I sure know I'm proud to be who I am.<br>
